note: Compact flare followed by some loop motion in AR 2360, but no apparent signs of CME.
Source location might be on or right behind the W limb judging by brightening in GOES-15 SXI and SDO.
There is definitely a possible eruption after the flare due to a big darkening area NE of AR 2371.

This AR has produced several flares already and is a Beta-Gamma-Delta AR.
We register another flare, 2015-06-21T02:06:00-FLR-001, as a separate flare, however these two flares can be considered as one long duration event with two peaks.

The same AR previously produced an M2.0 flare, 2015-06-21T01:02:00-FLR-001, which we register as a separate flare, however these two flares can be considered as one long duration event with two peaks.
Signs of CME-type structural evolution as well.
The source location was determined using GOES-P SXI due to a data gap in SDO.
Filament eruption seen associated with the flare in SDO 171/193/304
